Do's :
 -> Think before posting – Ensure your content is respectful and appropriate.
 -> Maintain privacy settings – Keep personal information secure and limit public access.
 -> Be respectful and polite – Communicate positively and avoid offensive language.
 -> Verify information before sharing – Check facts to avoid spreading misinformation.
 -> Build a positive digital footprint – Share achievements, skills, and meaningful content.

Dont's :
 -> Don’t share personal/sensitive information – Avoid posting phone numbers, addresses, or passwords.
 -> Don’t engage in cyberbullying or trolling – Respect others’ opinions and avoid negativity.
 -> Don’t post inappropriate or offensive content – It can harm your reputation and future opportunities.
 -> Don’t believe everything online blindly – Be cautious of fake news and scams.
 -> Don’t overshare – Keep a balance between online and personal life.


Tip : Always remember: “What goes online, stays online.”
